    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4041: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Fortes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 25, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Department’s telegram No. 17.<note n="22" xml:id="d235fn22">August 23, 8
                        p.m., <ref target="#pg_181">p. 181</ref>.</note> Message was delivered
                    Foreign Minister this afternoon. He commented that he understood from Finot that
                    the United States as well as Brazil is disposed to support Bolivia’s <hi
                        rend="italic">sine qua non</hi> condition. He wishes to know if in case
                    Paraguay should refuse condition whether the United States would not consider it
                    desirable to omit conciliation proceedings and go directly to arbitrate.</p>
                <p>Bolivia studying formula and will consult Brazil and United States before making
                    formal reply to Buenos Aires which will be delayed until after the return of the
                    President from a secret trip to Chaco.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Minister thanks you for interest and wishes United States Government
                    to know that Bolivia has a sincere desire for peace under honorable
                    conditions.</p>
                <p>Brazilian Minister at the request of Bolivian Minister for Foreign Affairs has
                    requested information through Rio de Janeiro to Buenos Aires regarding press
                    report military occupation by Argentina of several Chaco forts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
